        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​Asset> getAssetDetails()
        Details of the assets that exist in the lineage graph. The keys of the map are the unique identifiers (GUIDs) of each asset in lineage, and their value is an object containing the requested details for each asset. Note: this will always include both process and asset details.

      • setChildrenCounts

        @Deprecated
public void setChildrenCounts​(java.lang.Object childrenCounts)
        Deprecated.
        Mapping of assets to their upstream and downstream asset counts. In theory, the keys of the map are the unique identifiers (GUIDs) of each asset in lineage, and their value is an object containing a count of upstream INPUT and downstream OUTPUT assets in lineage from that asset. In reality, the INPUT count is missing for most assets. Note: this should not be used, instead traverse the graph representation.
